The paper deals with algorithms for matrix multiplication and graph problems in a distributed computing model, which suggests categories such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of sparse matrices and the focus on communication efficiency suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the mention of triangle listing and counting specifically suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
